   300	6. **Recovery / band edges** `G2↑`, `G3↑`, `ce`, `cc` (lowest).
   301	
   302	**Default rule:** if no listed event with a non-`·` cell is present, the state self-loops
   303	(authority and annunciation unchanged). Combined with the destination-function table above and
   304	the fail-safe invariant — *authority is granted only in N/C and only while `G1∧G2∧G3∧G4` all
   305	hold; the falling (false) of any grant term maps to a revoking transition or to a non-granting
   306	self-loop, never to a grant* — **every (state, event) cell resolves to exactly one successor**,
   307	with one authority result and one annunciation. This discharges the "every Boolean transition
   308	has exactly one outcome" obligation (finding 5) for all six states, including during
   309	WARNING/ESCALATED/LATCHED-SAFE and DISARMED.
   310	
   311	Note the distinction the previous draft missed: **G1 falling by helm command is an intended,
   312	quiet disarm** (→ D), while **G2/G3 false or G4 expiry are fault revocations that alarm** (→ W).
   313	"Any false term drops authority" still holds; only the *annunciation* differs by cause.
   314	Whole-process death (Case B) cannot self-annunciate — it presents to the helm via the absence of
   315	the healthy indication plus any independent annunciator, and to ArduPilot via the *absence* of
   316	`GPS_INPUT`, whose effect is `[UNVERIFIED]` (per D17 / U-M1; §2.1), not via a proven timeout
   317	action.
